frameDefinitions: An Employer employs an Employee whose Position entails that the Employee perform certain Tasks in exchange for Compensation.
A Member is semi-permanently part of a socially constructed Group.
A Defender responds to an Assailant's attack on a Victim by directly, and usually violently, countering it.
This frame contains nouns denoting Aggregates of Individuals.
This frame is concerned with transparent nouns denoting a Piece of a Substance.
A group of Individuals form a group, the Entourage, which remains co-located with the Attended_person.
frameExamples: I <t>employed</t> him as Chief Gardener for ten years.
Victor is <t>part</t> of the Red Crescent
Samantha stalwartly <t>defended</t> the gateway from the wraiths, crouching low over Stephen's prone form.
An <t><fex name='Agg'>army</fex></t> of postal workers descended on my office.
Kim ate a tiny <t><fex name='Piece'>morsel</fex></t> of cake
Just before eleven o'clock, one of the consultants came to do a ward round, followed by his <t><fex name='ent'>entourage</fex></t> of junior doctors and medical students.
listRoleDefinitions: The role <fen>Employee</fen> denotes the person who is obligated to perform some <fen>Task</fen> in order to receive <fen>Compensation</fen>.
The <fen>Employer</fen> is the person (or institution) that gives <fen>Compensation</fen> to an <fen>Employee</fen>.
The role <fen>Field</fen> identifies the field in which the <fen>Employee</fen> is employed.
The role <fen>Position</fen> indicates a particular type of employment.
The <fen>Task</fen> indicates the action/duty that the <fen>Employee</fen> is obligated to do for the <fen>Employer</fen>.
The role <fen>Time</fen> identifies the time at whcih the <fen>Employer</fen> hires the <fen>Employee</fen>.
The role <fen>Place</fen> identifies the location where the <fen>Employer</fen> hires the <fen>Employee</fen>.
The person who belongs to a <fen>Group</fen>.
A set of people standing in a semi-permanent relationship together.
The time at which the <fen>Member</fen> is a member of the <fen>Group</fen>.
The location where the membership relationship holds.
This role is the being or entity that responds forcefully to the <fen>Assailant</fen>'s attack.
The person (or other self-directed entity) that is attempting physical harm to the <fen>Victim</fen>.
The individual or entity that is under attack from the <fen>Assailant</fen> .
This role identifies the time when the Defender takes forceful action against the Assailant.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Defender</fen> defends the <fen>Victim</fen> from the <fen>Assailant</fen>.
This role identifies the people or things that form  the <fen>Aggregate</fen>.
This role identifies the collection of entities that are the <fen>Aggregate</fen>.
A <fen>Piece</fen> made of a substance.
The <fen>Substance</fen> is what the <fen>Piece</fen> is made of and may describe the type of larger whole from which it came.
This role identifies the people or things that form  the <fen>Entourage</fen>.
This role identifies the collection of entities that follow the Attended.
The <fen>Attended_person</fen> is followed by the <fen>Entourage</fen>.
listRoleExamples: <fex>I</fex> was employed by an international corporation.
<fex>I</fex> employed him as Chief Gardener for ten years.
He was employed<fex>in finance</fex> fourteen years ago.
I am employed <fex>to collect the trash</fex>.
Charles has been an employee of Microsoft <fex>since 1998</fex>!
Actually, he employed me <fex> at the downtown office </fex>.
Two <fex>members</fex> of the Red Cross were here about a donation
A crowd <fex>of hoodlums</fex> filled the plaza.
A <fex><t>crowd</t></fex> of hoodlums filled the plaza.
Sergey had a few <fex>morsels</fex> of bread for breakfast.
Just before eleven o'clock, one of the consultants came to do a ward round, followed by his entourage <fex>of junior doctors and medical students</fex>.
Most of the large <fex><t>entourage</t></fex> the president had brought with him quietly left him.
<fex>The lord's</fex> train consisted of several dozen servants, cooks, and other attendants.
